<a href="http://www.icco.org/about-us/icco-news/210-november-2012-quarterly-bulletin-of-cocoa-statistics.html" target="_self">http://www.icco.org/about-us/icco-news/210-november-2012-quarterly-bulle...</a></p><p>&nbsp;Agence Ecofin, ‘Jean-Marc Anga : « Nous sommes inquiets sur la durabilité de l’économie cacaoyère mondiale’, 9 August 2012</p><p>
<a href="http://www.agenceecofin.com/cacao/0811-7484-jean-marc-anga-nous-sommes-inquiets-sur-la-durabilite-de-l-economie-cacaoyere-mondiale " target="_self">http://www.agenceecofin.com/cacao/0811-7484-jean-marc-anga-nous-sommes-i...</a></p><p>Agence Ecofin, ‘Le Cameroun veut la peau de coxeurs et vise 600 000 tonnes de cacao en 2020’, 9 November 2012</p><p>
<a href="http://www.agenceecofin.com/cacao/0911-7499-le-cameroun-veut-la-peau-de-coxeurs-et-vise-600-000-tonnes-de-cacao-en-2020 " target="_self">http://www.agenceecofin.com/cacao/0911-7499-le-cameroun-veut-la-peau-de-...</a></p><p>Agence Ecofin, ‘Travail des enfants : Hershey en justice pour utilisation de cacao de Côte d’Ivoire et du Ghana’, 2 November 2012</p><p>
<a href="http://www.agenceecofin.com/industrie/0211-7386-travail-des-enfants-hershey-en-justice-pour-utilisation-de-cacao-de-cote-d-ivoire-et-du-ghana" target="_self">http://www.agenceecofin.com/industrie/0211-7386-travail-des-enfants-hers...</a></p>		</div>
		
		
				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>Cocoa farmers in West Africa are an aging population, as young farmers are not being attracted into the sector, despite the rising global demand and overall favourable price prospects. The potential for supply shortages is therefore causing concern among cocoa processing companies and end users. This has led to a range of corporate initiatives to support farmers’ organisations, boost production, improve bean quality and promote more sustainable forms of cocoa production.</p><p>Price volatility and rising input costs have led to renewed calls in producer countries for international cooperation to stabilise producer prices via minimum export price arrangements. While traditional approaches to export price stabilisation have long since fallen into disuse, there would appear to be a need to extend existing corporate initiatives on sustainable cocoa production to get to grips with economic and social sustainability issues faced by cocoa farmers, and to determine what role, if any, minimum producer price guarantees should play. This is still an area of considerable debate. Further discussions on how to ensure the economic and social sustainability of cocoa farming would appear to be necessary if the underlying lack of human and capital investment in cocoa production is to be addressed.</p><p>Intensified discussions would also appear to be necessary to explore how current technical and infrastructure constraints in ACP cocoa producing countries can be overcome, in order to promote more local value-added processing and enable more direct trading links to be established between ACP producers and expanding markets in Asia, in market components where this is appropriate. It needs to be borne in mind that the cocoa market is not homogenous, but is a highly differentiated market.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
		</div>
		
